      "href": "/stevenhou/list/art-horror/",
      "user": "stevenhou",
      "slug": "art-horror",
      "title": "Art Horror",
      "desc": "\"Art-horror films tend to rely more on atmosphere and style to create an unnerving experience than on actual “scares.” They may have characters or situations that lend themselves to typical horror narratives, but very often they work against viewer expectations by unfolding in elliptical ways, or keeping the actual horrors offscreen, or sending their stories in new, surreal directions.\"\nwww.vulture.com/2014/04/under-the-skin-and-a-history-of-art-horror-film.html\n\n* not an actually coherent grouping w/ hard and fast criteria. literally just #vibes at the moment. dont listen to my idiotic comments in the discussion section",
